  "prompt": "Cost for 1kg of A is 260 USD and 1kg of B is 380. AB is made by mixing A and B. If 1kg of AB costs 300, what was the ratio that A and B has mixed?",
  "response": "To find the ratio of A and B in the mixture AB, we can use a system of equations based on the cost of the components and the resulting mixture.\n\nLet \\( x \\) be the amount (in kg) of A used in the mixture and \\( y \\) be the amount (in kg) of B used. We know the following:\n\n1. The total mass of the mixture is 1 kg:\n   \\[\n   x + y = 1\n   \\]\n\n2. The total cost of the mixture is 300 USD, which can be expressed as:\n   \\[\n   260x + 380y = 300\n   \\]\n\nNow we have a system of equations:\n1. \\( x + y = 1 \\)\n2. \\( 260x + 380y = 300 \\)\n\nWe can solve these equations step-by-step.\n\nFrom the first equation, we can express \\( y \\) in terms of \\( x \\):\n\\[\ny = 1 - x\n\\]\n\nNow substitute \\( y \\) into the second equation:\n\\[\n260x + 380(1 - x) = 300\n\\]\n\nExpanding this gives:\n\\[\n260x + 380 - 380x = 300\n\\]\n\nCombine like terms:\n\\[\n-120x + 380 = 300\n\\]\n\nNow isolate \\( x \\):\n\\[\n-120x = 300 - 380\n\\]\n\\[\n-120x = -80\n\\]\n\\[\nx = \\frac{-80}{-120} = \\frac{2}{3}\n\\]\n\nNow substitute \\( x \\) back into the equation for \\( y \\):\n\\[\ny = 1 - x = 1 - \\frac{2}{3} = \\frac{1}{3}\n\\]\n\nThus, the amounts of A and B in the mixture are:\n- \\( x = \\frac{2}{3} \\) kg of A\n- \\( y = \\frac{1}{3} \\) kg of B\n\nThe ratio of A to B is:\n\\[\n\\frac{x}{y} = \\frac{\\frac{2}{3}}{\\frac{1}{3}} = \\frac{2}{1}\n\\]\n\nTherefore, the ratio of A to B in the mixture is \\( 2:1 \\).",
